---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Kenyan Hibiscus | Victoria Herbs & Spices – Premium Dried Hibiscus Flowers from Kenya"
  description="Kenyan Hibiscus (Hibiscus sabdariffa): Grown in Africa's highlands. Deep crimson calyces with intense cranberry flavor. Naturally tart, 100% sun-dried, and rich in antioxidants."
>
  <!-- Hero Section - The Crimson Bloom -->
  <section
    class="relative h-screen flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden"
  >
    <!-- Background with dramatic hibiscus image -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/hibiscus.jpg"
        alt="Vibrant crimson hibiscus flowers"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-rose-900/95 via-rose-900/80 to-rose-900/40"
      >
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-center">
      <!-- Heritage Badge -->
      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-rose-500/20 backdrop-blur-lg px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-rose-300 text-sm mb-8 border border-rose-500/30"
      >
        <span class="relative flex h-3 w-3">
          <span
            class="animate-ping absolute inline-flex h-full w-full rounded-full bg-rose-400 opacity-75"
          ></span>
          <span class="relative inline-flex rounded-full h-3 w-3 bg-rose-500"
          ></span>
        </span>
        <span>🇰🇪 Kenya Highlands • 100% Sun-Dried</span>
        <span class="text-white/50 mx-2">•</span>
        <span>🌺 Since 2018</span>
      </div>

      <h1
        class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-display font-bold text-white leading-tight"
      >
        Nature's<br />
        <span
          class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-rose-400 to-pink-500"
        >
          Crimson Treasure
        </span>
      </h1>

      <p
        class="mt-6 text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/90 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
      >
        Grown in Kenya's pristine highlands — where cool mountain air,
        mineral-rich soils, and generations of farming wisdom produce hibiscus
        calyces of exceptional color, flavor, and antioxidant potency.
      </p>

      <!-- Color Intensity Scale -->
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-12">
        <div class="flex justify-between text-xs text-white/50 mb-2">
          <span>Pale Pink</span>
          <span>Light Red</span>
          <span>Standard Red</span>
          <span class="text-rose-400 font-bold">Kenyan Crimson</span>
          <span>Deep Purple</span>
        </div>
        <div
          class="h-3 bg-stone-800/50 rounded-full overflow-hidden backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div
            class="h-full w-3/4 bg-gradient-to-r from-rose-400 via-red-500 to-rose-600 relative"
            style="width: 85%"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute right-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-white animate-pulse"
            >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-white/50 text-xs mt-2">
          Color intensity = anthocyanin content • Our hibiscus tests at 95%+
          color retention
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5 justify-center mt-16">
        <a
          href="#the-crimson-difference"
          class="group px-8 py-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-rose-500 to-pink-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl hover:from-rose-600 hover:to-pink-700 transition-all shadow-lg shadow-rose-600/20 inline-flex items-center gap-2"
        >
          Discover the Difference
          <svg
            class="w-5 h-5 group-hover:translate-y-1 transition-transform"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              stroke-width="2"
              d="M19 14l-7 7-7-7m14-6l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/contact?quote=true&product=hibiscus"
          class="px-8 py-4 border-2 border-white/30 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl hover:bg-white/10 hover:border-white/50 transition backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          Request Sample
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scroll Indicator -->
    <div
      class="absolute bottom-8 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 flex flex-col items-center text-white/40 text-xs tracking-widest"
    >
      <span>SCROLL TO DISCOVER</span>
      <div
        class="w-px h-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-white/30 to-transparent mt-2"
      >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Crimson Difference -->
  <section id="the-crimson-difference" class="py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <span
            class="text-rose-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
            >The Crimson Difference</span
          >
          <h2
            class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4 text-stone-900 leading-tight"
          >
            Why Kenyan Hibiscus<br />Wears the Crown
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-6 mt-8 text-stone-700">
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              Not all hibiscus is created equal. The <span
                class="font-bold text-rose-600">Hibiscus sabdariffa</span
              > variety grown in Kenya's highlands produces calyces with deeper color,
              more intense flavor, and higher concentrations of anthocyanins — the
              powerful antioxidants responsible for the deep crimson hue and health
              benefits.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              The secret lies in <span class="font-semibold">terroir</span>:
              cool nights slow maturation, allowing complex flavor compounds to
              develop, while intense equatorial sun drives anthocyanin
              production as the plant's natural protection against UV radiation.
              The result? A hibiscus that's visually stunning, flavorfully
              complex, and nutritionally superior.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Anthocyanin Comparison -->
          <div
            class="mt-10 bg-gradient-to-r from-rose-50 to-pink-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-rose-200"
          >
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-4">
              Anthocyanin Content Comparison
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span>Standard Hibiscus</span>
                  <span>100-150 mg/100g</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-3 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div
                    class="h-full w-[40%] bg-rose-300 rounded-full"
                    style="width: 40%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span>Premium Grade</span>
                  <span>150-200 mg/100g</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-3 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div
                    class="h-full w-[60%] bg-rose-400 rounded-full"
                    style="width: 60%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">🇰🇪 Kenyan Highland</span
                  >
                  <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">280-320 mg/100g</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-3 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div
                    class="h-full w-[95%] bg-rose-600 rounded-full"
                    style="width: 95%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-4">
              *Independent lab analysis shows 2x higher antioxidant content
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Terroir Cards -->
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-rose-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">⛰️</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  Highland Altitude (1,500-2,000m)
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  Grown in the cool highlands of Meru and Kiambu, our hibiscus
                  experiences temperature swings of 15°C between day and night.
                  This stress triggers anthocyanin production, resulting in
                  deeper crimson color and higher antioxidant content.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-rose-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">🌋</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  Volcanic Red Soils
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  Kenya's famous red volcanic soils are rich in iron and trace
                  minerals. These nutrients are absorbed by the hibiscus plants,
                  contributing to deeper pigmentation and more complex flavor
                  profiles.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-rose-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">💧</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  Bimodal Rainfall
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  Two rainy seasons (March-May and October-December) allow for
                  two harvests annually, each producing calyces with slightly
                  different flavor profiles — the long rains crop is more
                  robust, the short rains crop more delicate.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-rose-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">☀️</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  UV-Rich Equatorial Sun
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  At the equator, UV intensity is 40% higher than temperate
                  regions. Hibiscus plants respond by producing more
                  anthocyanins — nature's sunscreen — resulting in calyces with
                  exceptional color density.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Flavor Profile -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-gradient-to-b from-rose-900 to-pink-900 text-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <span
          class="text-rose-300 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
          >Taste the Highlands</span
        >
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4">
          A Symphony of Flavor
        </h2>
        <p class="text-white/70 text-lg mt-4">
          Kenyan hibiscus isn't just tart — it's complex. Here's what you'll
          taste in every cup.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 text-center"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🍒</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Cranberry-Cherry</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Bright, upfront tartness reminiscent of fresh cranberries with
            subtle cherry undertones.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 text-center"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🍷</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Red Wine Notes</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Complex, slightly tannic finish that wine connoisseurs compare to
            young Cabernet.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 text-center"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🌸</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Floral Undertones</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Delicate rose and hibiscus blossom notes that linger on the palate.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 text-center"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🍊</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Citrus Brightness</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Hints of orange zest and lemon that balance the deep berry flavors.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Brewing Guide -->
      <div
        class="mt-16 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-md p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/20"
      >
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">
          Perfect Brewing Guide
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="text-4xl mb-2">🌡️</div>
            <div class="font-bold">Temperature</div>
            <div class="text-white/70">100°C (212°F)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="text-4xl mb-2">⏱️</div>
            <div class="font-bold">Steep Time</div>
            <div class="text-white/70">5-7 minutes</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="text-4xl mb-2">🥤</div>
            <div class="font-bold">Ratio</div>
            <div class="text-white/70">1 tbsp per cup</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-center text-white/60 text-sm mt-6">
          For iced tea, double the flowers and steep longer — the flavor
          intensifies as it chills.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Harvest Story -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <span
            class="text-rose-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
            >From Field to Cup</span
          >
          <h2
            class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4 text-stone-900"
          >
            The Art of Harvesting Hibiscus
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-6 mt-8">
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-700">
              Unlike other crops, hibiscus requires <span
                class="font-bold text-rose-600">perfect timing</span
              >. The calyces — the fleshy red part surrounding the seed pod —
              must be harvested at exactly the right moment: not too early
              (pale, underdeveloped flavor), not too late (woody, less vibrant).
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-700">
              Our farmers harvest by hand, selecting only the deepest crimson
              calyces. Each plant is visited multiple times during the season,
              as flowers mature at different rates. This labor-intensive process
              ensures every calyx meets our export standards.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Harvest Calendar -->
          <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-rose-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
              <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-600">March-May</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-stone-600">
                Long Rains Harvest<br />Bolder, more robust
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-rose-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
              <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-600">Oct-Dec</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-stone-600">
                Short Rains Harvest<br />Delicate, floral notes
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Farmer Quote -->
          <div
            class="mt-10 bg-rose-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-rose-500"
          >
            <p class="text-stone-700 italic">
              "You have to wake before dawn. The calyzes are most vibrant in the
              early morning light. My grandmother taught me: 'If it bleeds like
              wine, it's time. If it's pale like water, wait another week.'"
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 font-semibold text-stone-900">— Njoki Wambui</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500">
              Hibiscus farmer, Meru County • 3rd generation
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1629819109533-9d0fb5b6c972?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80"
            alt="Fresh hibiscus harvest"
            class="rounded-2xl shadow-xl w-full h-64 object-cover"
          />
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563911892437-1feda0179e1b?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80"
            alt="Drying hibiscus"
            class="rounded-2xl shadow-xl w-full h-64 object-cover mt-8"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Drying Process -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <span
          class="text-rose-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
          >Traditional Methods</span
        >
        <h2
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4 text-stone-900"
        >
          Sun-Dried with Care
        </h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg mt-4">
          Mechanical drying destroys color and flavor. Our hibiscus is slowly
          dried under the sun, a traditional process that preserves the deep
          crimson hue and delicate flavor compounds.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4 text-rose-500">☀️</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">5-7 Days in Sun</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">
            Spread on raised mesh racks for maximum airflow. Turned twice daily
            for even drying.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4 text-rose-500">🌙</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Night Coverage</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">
            Protected from dew and overnight moisture to prevent mold and color
            degradation.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4 text-rose-500">👐</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Hand-Sorted</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">
            Each batch is hand-sorted by our women's cooperative — removing
            stems, seeds, and any imperfect calyces.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-rose-600 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6"
        >
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Moisture Content: ≤12%</h4>
            <p class="text-rose-100">
              Perfect for long-term storage without mold or quality loss
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Color Retention: 95%+</h4>
            <p class="text-rose-100">
              Sun-drying preserves the vibrant crimson color buyers expect
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Shelf Life: 24 months</h4>
            <p class="text-rose-100">When stored in cool, dry conditions</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Health Benefits -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <span
          class="text-rose-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
          >Nature's Pharmacy</span
        >
        <h2
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4 text-stone-900"
        >
          More Than Just a Pretty Flower
        </h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg mt-4">
          Hibiscus has been used in traditional African medicine for centuries.
          Modern science confirms what our grandmothers knew.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-3">❤️</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Heart Health</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
            Studies show hibiscus tea may help maintain healthy blood pressure
            levels.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🛡️</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Antioxidant Rich</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
            High in anthocyanins and flavonoids that combat oxidative stress.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-3">⚡</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Vitamin C</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
            Natural source of immune-supporting vitamin C.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌡️</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Cooling Properties</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
            Traditionally consumed as a refreshing, cooling beverage in hot
            climates.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Product Forms -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-stone-900">
          Choose Your Form
        </h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg mt-4">
          We offer Kenyan hibiscus in multiple formats to suit your
          manufacturing, blending, or retail needs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Whole Flowers -->
        <div
          class="group bg-white rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition border border-stone-200"
        >
          <div class="h-56 overflow-hidden">
            <img
              src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1629819109533-9d0fb5b6c972?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80"
              alt="Whole dried hibiscus flowers"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-700"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="p-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">
              Whole Flowers
            </h3>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">
              Premium whole calyces, stems and seeds removed. Perfect for tea
              blends, retail packaging, and beverage manufacturing.
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">MOQ:</span><span
                  class="font-medium">25kg</span
                >
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
